This is a transcript of President Donald Trump's remarks at the Susan B. Anthony List Gala held on May 22, 2018. In his speech, President Trump thanked various individuals and politicians for their support and highlighted his administration's efforts to protect life, including the reinstatement of the Mexico City Policy and the proposed rule to prohibit Title 10 funding from going to clinics that perform abortions. He also discussed the need to elect more lawmakers who share their values and vote their agenda, and urged supporters to campaign and vote in the upcoming midterm elections. President Trump emphasized the importance of standing for life and protecting the rights of the unborn, and praised the adoption of a child by Lisa and Bruce Alexander as an example of the loving choice of adoption. He concluded his speech by urging people to vote for family, love, faith, values, and country.